libquicktime: libquicktime
libquicktime:
libquicktime: libquicktime is a library for reading and writing quicktime
libquicktime: files. It is based on the quicktime4linux library,
libquicktime: with the following extensions: * Sourcetree upgraded with
libquicktime: autoconf/automake/libtool and all the other stuff, people like
libquicktime: in "standard" linux libraries.  * All 3rd party libraries
libquicktime: (jpeg, OggVorbis) were removed to reduce download size,
libquicktime: compilation time and code duplication on users harddisks.
libquicktime: Instead, the sytemwide installed libaries are autodetected
libquicktime: by the configure script.
